'''Corporate poverty''' is the practice of refusing to own property, either individually or corporately. This practice of [[Middle Ages]] [[Religious order|religious communities]] developed based on [[Christian]] religious beliefs. Practical considerations generally allow for some exceptions.<ref Name="Johnston">{{cite book |title= Encyclopedia of monasticism, Volume 1 |last= Johnston |first= William M. |authorlink= William M. Johnston |coauthors= |year= 2000 |publisher= Taylor & Francis |location= |isbn= 1-57958-090-4 |page= 429 |pages= |url= https://books.google.com/books?id=GfC0TDkJJNgC&pg=PA429&dq=%22Corporate+poverty%22&as_brr=3&client=firefox-a&cd=4#v=onepage&q=%22Corporate%20poverty%22&f=false}}</ref>
