[[File:Ants eating.jpg|thumb|The eating behavior of ants as a sign of what is to be]]
{{wiktionary|myrmomancy}}
'''Myrmomancy''' (from Greek ''myrmex'' "ant" and ''manteia'' "prophecy") is the practice of reading [[omen]]s from the observed behavior of [[ant]]s, especially from their eating behavior. It is a form of '''entomomancy''' (from Greek ''entomon'' "insect"), which is itself [[Methods of divination#T|theriomantic]] (from Greek ''therion'' "wild beast"; also known as "zoomancy"). People who use this [[divination]] technique subscribe to the worldview that the movements of ants are, in some supernatural way, ultimately connected with their life and that an understanding of these movements enables one to learn about the future. The interpretation of ant behavior may vary cross-culturally.

